@section Introduction to etags

A @emph{TAGS} file is a structured database holding information about
source-code, see
@indicateurl{https://secure.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/wiki/Ctags}. The
source code editors @emph{Emacs}, @emph{VI} and others, have in-built
facilities to use TAGS files.

@node Functions and Variables for etags,  , Introduction to etags, etags
@section Functions and Variables for etags

All global variables in Lisp special variables interned in the
@code{etags} package. Although the user can change them using the
special syntax @code{:lisp (setf etags::*foo*)} @xref{Keyword Commands},
it is preferable to pass options to the @code{etags} command.

@defvr {Global variable} *etags-regex-maxima-list*

@var{*etags-regex-maxima-list*} is the default list of regular
expressions to tag Maxima source code. It is a @emph{Lisp} special
variable in the @code{etags} package. There should be no reason to
change this variable.

